# Editing src/

Project-specific rules when changing files under `src/`. Apply together with
`minimal-and-safe-editing.mdc`. Architecture and operator detail live in
`docs/` and `AGENTS.md`; this file is agent editing constraints only.

## Runtime

- Require Node.js 26+.
- Run TypeScript source directly with Node type stripping.
- Use erasable TypeScript syntax only: no enums, namespaces, or parameter
  properties.
- Use `.ts` extensions in relative ESM imports.

## Structure

Allowed top-level folders under `src/`:

- `src/git/`
- `src/types/`
- `src/mirror-init/`
- `src/mirror-poll/`
- `src/mirror-sync/`
- `src/mirror-merge/`

Do not add new top-level folders under `src/` without discussing with the
maintainer first.

- Stage entry points: `src/mirror-*/cli.ts`.
- Shared git helpers: `src/git/*.ts`.
- Shared sync types: `src/types/*.ts`.
- Config defaults: `config/mirror-merge.json`; scripts read config and do not write it.

## Mirror stage modules

Stages under `src/mirror-init/`, `src/mirror-poll/`, `src/mirror-sync/`, and
`src/mirror-merge/` are self-contained pipeline stages. Each stage owns its CLI
entry (`cli.ts`), config, and every helper used only by that stage.

### Allowed cross-module imports

Only these paths may be imported from outside the stage directory:

- `../git/*` -- git subprocess helpers and `Logger`
- `../types/*` -- shared types and constants (e.g. `mirror-sync-config`)

Do not add new entries to this list (or new allowed cross-module import paths in
code) without discussing with the maintainer first.

Also allowed:

- Node.js built-ins
- Relative imports within the same stage (`./config.ts`, `./tooling-digest.ts`, ...)

### Forbidden imports

Do not import:

- Any other stage (`../mirror-init/*`, `../mirror-poll/*`, `../mirror-sync/*`,
  `../mirror-merge/*`)
- Any other top-level `src/*` tree not listed in Structure (no `../lib/*`,
  `../cli/*`, ...)

### Where helpers belong

- **One stage only:** keep the module in that stage directory (e.g.
  `src/mirror-init/tooling-digest.ts`, `src/mirror-merge/queue.ts`).
- **Two or more stages:** shared types and constants in `src/types/`; git
  subprocess wrappers in `src/git/`.
- **Do not** add `src/lib/` or cross-import between stages. Do not move a helper
  out of a stage until a second stage actually needs it.

## Git Replay

- Use the `git` CLI only.
- Preserve upstream author metadata in `GIT_AUTHOR_*`.
- Preserve upstream committer metadata in `GIT_COMMITTER_*`.
- Message body is LF only and follows the template in `config/mirror-merge.json` (`Sources[].CommitMessage`).
- On failure mid-batch, stop without pushing; re-run without `--clean` to continue from branch cursors.
- First replayed commit parent is `config/mirror-merge.json` -> `Destination.BaseCommit`.
- Bootstrap when any sync branch is missing; `--clean` resets sync branches first.

## Logging

- Print progress with `[sync]`, `[sync][warn]`, and `[sync][error]`.
- Exit non-zero on failure; exit zero when there is nothing to do or sync
  succeeds.

## External Tools

- Required: `git`.
- Optional in CI: `gh` for upstream SHA checks.
